description:
&lt;p&gt;STAFF COUNSELLOR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(part-time/substantive – 3 days a week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 6: £33,176- 37,890 (pro rata)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inclusive of high cost area allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to join CONTACT – the Staff Counselling Stress Management, Conflict Resolution and Trauma Support Service for Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust, based at 3 major hospitals: Charing Cross, Hammersmith and St. Mary’s. CONTACT is a comprehensive support service for staff at all levels of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a BACP/UKCP/BPS accredited practitioner with at least two years post qualification and substantive experience with a wide range of clients and time-limited work. You will have group facilitation skills, confidence in working with trauma and have experience of workplace counselling and workplace issues. Integrated transcultural approach essential. You will be working at 2 of the major hospitals and may be required to work at all 3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like an informal discussion about the post phone the CONTACT team on 020 331 32747/21519&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
